Pop the @diced sweet potato{300%g} on a #baking tray{} and drizzle on a splash of
@oil{a splash}. Season with @salt{} and the @Mexican style spice mix{1%tsp},
toss to combine. Roast in the #oven{} until soft and golden, ~{15-18%minutes}.
Turn halfway through cooking.

Heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. When
hot, brown the @coconut & chilli marinated chicken breast{280%g} for
~{2-3%minutes} on each side, then transfer to the #baking tray{} in the oven.
Roast the chicken until the middle is no longer pink, ~{12-14%minutes}. Wipe
out the frying pan we will use it again in a moment.

Meanwhile, halve the @cherry plum tomatoes{200%g}. Roughly chop the @coriander{10%g}(stalks and all). Zest then halve the @lime{1/2}. Drain and rinse the
@black beans{1}.

When the chicken and sweet potato have 5 mins left, heat a splash of
@oil{a splash} in the frying pan over medium-high heat. Add the cherry
tomatoes, cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the @garlic cloves{2}(minced), stir and
cook for ~{2%minutes}. Next add the black beans. Cook for another
~{2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Share the bean jumble between your #bowls{}. Top with the roasted sweet potato
chunks. Slice the chicken and arrange on top. Finish by crumbling on the
@feta cheese{100%g}. Enjoy!

> The marinade on the chicken provides a great sweetness to this dish that works
> perfectly alongside the heat from the fajita seasoning. All ready in the
> shake of a mariachi band's maracas.